## 6. RESTRICTIONS & COMPATIBILITY:
restrictions:
  max_io_current: "500mA"
  total_current_limit: "1500mA"
  warnings[7]:
    - "Digital outputs (MOSFET) have NO overload or short-circuit protection — always install external fuses or breakers rated for the load; a short circuit on any DO will permanently damage the output MOSFET driver; use 0.5A fuses per output channel"
    - "PTO pulse train output is fully supported on this DC/DC/DC variant — Qa.0-Qa.3 support up to 100kHz; Qa.4 supports up to 20kHz; use MC_MoveAbsolute/MC_MoveRelative/MC_MoveVelocity with an external PULSE+DIR drive"
    - "The 2 built-in analog inputs (AIW0, AIW2) support ONLY 0-10VDC — there is NO built-in current (4-20mA) input; to measure 4-20mA, add an external shunt resistor (500 ohm precision) across the analog input; alternatively install SM1231 AI or SB1231 AI for true current inputs with proper isolation"
    - "The built-in analog inputs have NO isolation from the CPU logic — always use shielded and twisted pair cables (max 100m) and connect the shield at only one end (preferably the PLC end) to avoid ground loops; floating signal sources require a reference connection to M terminal of the CPU sensor supply"
    - "The 5VDC backplane bus for expansion modules is limited to 1600mA total — each SM draws approximately 40-200mA from the backplane; if the total current exceeds 1600mA a Power Module PM1207 must be inserted between SMs; always calculate the backplane current budget before selecting expansion modules"
    - "The RTC backup uses an internal supercapacitor (no battery) that provides approximately 480 hours (20 days) of clock backup after power loss — for longer retention the SB1297 Battery Board must be installed in the Signal Board slot; installing SB1297 permanently occupies the SB slot and prevents use of other Signal Boards simultaneously"
    - "OPC UA server is available from firmware V4.4 and TIA Portal V16 — older firmware versions do NOT support OPC UA; before enabling OPC UA ensure the CPU firmware is updated; OPC UA requires a security certificate to be configured in TIA Portal and deployed to the CPU; unsecured OPC UA is disabled by default from V4.4"
compatibility:
  sw: "STEP 7 Basic V11+ / TIA Portal V11+; TIA Portal Professional V13+ for full SCL and advanced motion; STEP 7 V5.x NOT compatible"
  languages: "Ladder Diagram (LAD);Function Block Diagram (FBD);Structured Control Language (SCL);Sequential Function Chart (SFC via STEP 7 SFC blocks)"
  frameworks: "IEC61131-3;TIA Portal;PROFINET;Modbus-TCP-RTU;S7-comm;OPC-UA;Web-Server;PROFIBUS-via-CM"
  certifications: "CE;cULus;UL;FM;RCM;EAC;UKCA;Marine (DNV-GL)"

